quizzes.question:
Fill in the blanks to make the text of the "colored" class green:
[!raw!]
p.{0} {
{1}: {2};
}

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]The color Property[/h1]

The CSS [b]color[/b] property specifies the color of the text.
One method of specifying the color of the text is using a [b]color name[/b]: like red, green, blue, etc. 
Here's an example of changing the color of your font.

[b]The HTML:[/b] [code format="html" ]<p class="example">The text inside the paragraph is green.</p>
The text outside the paragraph is black (by default). [/code]
[b]The CSS:[/b] [code format="css" codeId="519"]p.example {
   [b]color[/b]: green;
}[/code]
